abstract: The president’s order would allow the government to withhold money from campuses deemed to be biased, but critics see it as an attack on free speech.
snippet: The president’s order would allow the government to withhold money from campuses deemed to be biased, but critics see it as an attack on free speech.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump plans to sign an executive order on Wednesday targeting what he sees as anti-Semitism on college campuses by threatening to withhold federal money from educational institutions that fail to combat discrimination, three administration officials said on Tuesday.

abstract: Thousands of UK political ads went missing from Facebook Inc's searchable advertising database on Tuesday, hampering researchers' ability to track ads two days before Britain's general election.
snippet: Thousands of UK political ads went missing from Facebook Inc's searchable advertising database on Tuesday, hampering researchers' ability to track ads two days before Britain's general election.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Thousands of UK political ads went missing from Facebook Inc's searchable advertising database on Tuesday, hampering researchers' ability to track ads two days before Britain's general election.
headline_main: Thousands of UK Political Ads Went Missing From Facebook Archive Searches

abstract: The former campaign aide cooperated with prosecutors on high-profile cases including the trials of Paul Manafort and Roger Stone.
snippet: The former campaign aide cooperated with prosecutors on high-profile cases including the trials of Paul Manafort and Roger Stone.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Federal prosecutors said in a court filing on Tuesday that despite his long litany of crimes, the former Trump campaign aide Rick Gates deserved leniency because he provided incriminating information against powerful figures amid intense pressure, including promises of payments if he refused to cooperate with investigators.

abstract: In the waning weeks before South Carolina's presidential primary, Democrat Tom Steyer is renewing his focus on the black voters who play a pivotal role in the first-in-the-South state, rolling out a proposal to improve historically black colleges and institutions.
snippet: In the waning weeks before South Carolina's presidential primary, Democrat Tom Steyer is renewing his focus on the black voters who play a pivotal role in the first-in-the-South state, rolling out a proposal to improve historically black colleges ...
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — In the waning weeks before South Carolina's presidential primary, Democrat Tom Steyer is renewing his focus on the black voters who play a pivotal role in the first-in-the-South state, rolling out a proposal to improve historically black colleges and institutions.
headline_main: In South Carolina, Steyer Investing in Black Voters
headline_print_headline: In South Carolina, Steyer Investing in Black Voters

abstract: One of the most influential Catholic theologians of the 20th century, he challenged his fellow German Catholics to face the reality of Auschwitz.
snippet: One of the most influential Catholic theologians of the 20th century, he challenged his fellow German Catholics to face the reality of Auschwitz.
lead_paragraph: Johann Baptist Metz, one of the most influential Roman Catholic theologians of the 20th century and a pioneer of Jewish-Christian dialogue in the aftermath of the Holocaust, died on Dec. 2 in Münster, Germany. He was 91.

abstract: Brazil's Senate took a step on Tuesday toward restoring mandatory imprisonment for convicts after they lose their first appeal, a move that could return former leftist President Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva to jail for corruption.
snippet: Brazil's Senate took a step on Tuesday toward restoring mandatory imprisonment for convicts after they lose their first appeal, a move that could return former leftist President Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva to jail for corruption.
lead_paragraph: BRASILIA — Brazil's Senate took a step on Tuesday toward restoring mandatory imprisonment for convicts after they lose their first appeal, a move that could return former leftist President Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva to jail for corruption.
headline_main: Brazil Senate Advances Bill That Could Put Lula Back in Jail
headline_print_headline: Brazil Senate Advances Bill That Could Put Lula Back in Jail

abstract: Genaro García Luna once served in a presidential cabinet and as the head of Mexico’s equivalent of the F.B.I. He was indicted in New York on charges of taking bribes while in office.
snippet: Genaro García Luna once served in a presidential cabinet and as the head of Mexico’s equivalent of the F.B.I. He was indicted in New York on charges of taking bribes while in office.
lead_paragraph: A retired Mexican police official who once led his country’s equivalent of the F.B.I. was indicted in New York on Tuesday on charges of taking bribes while in office to protect the Sinaloa drug cartel, one of Mexico’s most powerful criminal mafias.
